The Stripe Model Context Protocol (MCP) server allows AI agents to interact with the Stripe API and documentation using standardized function calling [1][2]. You can connect to Stripe’s remotely hosted MCP server at https://mcp.stripe.com or run it locally using the @stripe/mcp package [1][3][4].

For remote connections, OAuth is the recommended authentication method [1][5]. For local installations or agentic software, you can use a restricted API key as a bearer token [1][6].

To run the server locally via npx:
```bash
npx -y @stripe/mcp --api-key=YOUR_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
```

To configure it in your MCP client configuration file:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "stripe": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@stripe/mcp", "--api-key=YOUR_STRIPE_SECRET_KEY"]
    }
  }
}
```

The server provides tools for managing customers, products, invoices, refunds, and balances, as well as searching Stripe’s documentation [1][7][4][8].
